What is GRUB?

GRUB stands for GRand Unified Bootloader.

Itâ€™s the program that starts first when your PC turns on and decides which OS or kernel to boot.

ğŸ¤– What GRUB Does

When your computer starts:

BIOS/UEFI runs.
GRUB loads from MBR or EFI partition.
GRUB shows you a boot menu (if more than 1 OS or kernel).
You choose (or it auto-boots the default).
GRUB loads the Linux kernel â†’ Linux starts!

ğŸ§± GRUB Boot Flow (Simple Diagram)

=============================================
											|
BIOS/UEFI									|
   â†“										|
