ğŸ’¬ Extra Tips

To see GRUB menu, press Shift (BIOS) or Esc (UEFI) during boot.
You can edit a boot entry temporarily by pressing e in the GRUB menu.
You can boot into recovery mode from GRUB â†’ "Advanced options for Linux".
